textAfterTable: Mahlknecht appeared in all 31 games, making 20 starts, during her freshman season … averaged 5.1 points and 4.3 rebounds on the season … finished second in the Big West Conference with 45 blocks on the season, the fourth-most in school history for a single season … had a season-high five rejections in a home win over UC Irvine … scored in double-figures five times during the season, including a season-high 14 points and seven field goals at Oregon State … had two games with double-figure rebounds, including a season-high 13 boards in a home win over San Jose State … also had season-high five free throws against the Spartans … dished out season-high four assists against Long Beach State … added 27 assists and 18 steals during rookie season.  Agoura Hills High School Mahlknecht was a four-year starter and team captain during her senior season with the Chargers and Steve Scifres ... earned numerous awards after her senior season, including First Team All-CIF, All-Marmonte League and All-Ventura County honors ... part of two consecutive league championship teams ... graduated in 2011.
